snippet.textDisplay:
A year ago, I never thought the boys I stumbled into during the Say My Name era would mean so much to me, or would have come this far. When it comes to music and K-Pop, a LOT of things fall out of my radar. But I've stayed on top of all the ATEEZ news since discovering them, and there hasn't been a single comeback that I didn't like, and I listened to almost all of their songs. After Wonderland and All to Action, I thought: how could they ever top THAT?


I was wrong, and I'm glad that I was. I don't know how they manage to keep getting better and better. These kids are still so young and have remarkable talent, but are still so incredibly mature, creatively ambitious and humble for their age. KQ Entertainment is raising these boys right, and I'm so grateful they have such caring staff to take care of them and collaborate with them on their journey. I genuinely believe that their stage presence has gotten better, their confidence in their performance has gotten better, and I'm so appreciative as a fan to have seen this growth on their journey.


Their music was what helped me survive 2019, and there's no doubt in my mind that where ever ATEEZ go from here, I will follow them and their music.

Hi! I’m your official conspiracy theory clown atiny!
Here is my latest conspiracy theory (I have a lot more, but I’m to lazy to write them all. And if I did, this comment would be as long as those comments who make you scroll forever to reach the end)🤠:

I think they were looking at their past selves (them in black clothing and hats), and looking back at how they traveled through their journey. They were looking back because now they’re celebrating that they have found the answer they’ve been searching for; the reason they journeyed so far. (Now here comes where I got the conspiracy). The snippets in both the beginning of the video and the end show a person in a mask walking around in the room where they were celebrating in earlier in the video. The room was trashed, chairs were everywhere, the chandelier is in the table (I assume it fell), there’s stuff flying in the air (idk if it’s dust, snow, ash, or something else). I think that sometime (idk when) after they celebrated, they were attacked (they could have been ambushed or they knew the attack was coming). That’s when they had the battle. Of course they were in a building, maybe a mansion since the room looked very fancy and expensive. I would assume the rest of the building or majority if it was also trashed and destroyed. The person in those two small snippets wearing white and a mask, I assume that was one of the members. There are two that it can it to for this one conspiracy theory:

1. The member that was there, was there because after the battle, the others disappeared and so did the enemy. That member was there looking for clues as to where his friends went and where the enemy fled to. ( before we go further I’ll say this now: he [the member that was left] was wearing white because others had celebrated about “destroying and killing the enemy”, and at the same time mourning the loss of the other members. After that celebration he went to the mansion [thats what I think the building was] to look for clues) — That’s why he was looking at the objects left in the room, and just walking around.

2. This goes for what I said in ‘1.’, the member jut went to mansion to mourn after the celebration that just happened. In this part the other members did die, and the enemy, again, fled somewhere and hid. This time, the member was their to both mourn and to find clues on where the enemy fled to. He’s looking for clues to find the enemy so he can avenge his fellow who sadly died during and after the battle.

Now here’s my praise to them:
ATEEZ did so well, I died. I am Seonghwa biased, and let me tell you... He was MADE for the parts they gave him. When Yeosang suddenly came up I almost screamed so loudly, and I almost had a heart attack. He’s so BEAUTIFUL. San literally had me dead with those clips of him dancing in the table. I wish I was the table 😀. Yunho and his VOICE, kill me please. Hongjoong with his white hair and the way he danced.. I can’t even rn. Mingi... when he rapped I swear I saw the light. Jongho actually blessed my ears once more with his high note and whistle note. I cry because of this. Wooyoung was too hot, why did the stylists have to give him that shirt? They knew we would die. They knew. (Honestly same you Seonghwa tho, his shirt was actually see through.)

In conclusion: I am a clown for making this conspiracy along with others. I suspect that their next title track might be ‘Aftermath’, ‘it’s not over’, ‘the end’, ‘battle’, or something similar to those titles (this just proves once more how much of a clown I am, but anyway). ATEEZ once again killed me. Seonghwa actually wants me dead, he is so aware of the power he holds. I practically made their next in my head (no joke I already thought of the beat, the mv and mv aesthetic, choreography [not all of it], outfits, hair, makeup, lyrics [genralizing the lyrics at this point], line distribution, and the b-sides with their own special clips and scenes.) I’m too extra for this 😀. And I stan and love ATEEZ even more now!

Official conspiracy theory clown of the atiny fandom, signing out!
